.worktrees/

# Git submodules are foreign nested repos, not this repo's source. ripgrep
# descends into each anyway: once it hits the submodule's own `.git`, it treats
# that dir as a fresh repo root and stops honoring the parent's .gitignore rules
# (notably the repo-wide `**/*.md` ignore). That leak makes folder-keyword
# searches drown in another project's markdown/state. Listing the submodules
# here closes it. Mirrors the "foreign trees" section of .ckignore.
#
# Measured impact (folder-keyword file counts, base @ dev-manu, before -> after):
#   status     1673 -> 523   (-1150)
#   terminal   1200 -> 587   ( -613)
#   node       4922 -> 2283  (-2639)
#   graph      2928 -> 1877  (-1051)
# packages/ + webapp/ source hits are unchanged — only foreign-repo noise is removed.
voicetree-evals/
vt-website-quartz/
